<subSubSection id="44911484C502BD42FF15F963559BFEA8" lastPageId="19" lastPageNumber="250" pageId="18" pageNumber="249" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph id="0C34470FC502BD43FF15F9635220F850" blockId="18.[151,1437,1743,2021]" pageId="18" pageNumber="249">
<emphasis id="3EFF9B1DC502BD43FF15F963507FF95C" bold="true" box="[151,279,1743,1769]" pageId="18" pageNumber="249">Type data:</emphasis>
This species was described from male and female specimens collected in 
<collectingCountry id="749C079FC502BD43FBD6F96355F9F95C" box="[1108,1169,1743,1769]" name="Chile" pageId="18" pageNumber="249">Chile</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry id="749C079FC502BD43FB45F9635475F95C" box="[1223,1309,1743,1769]" name="Bolivia" pageId="18" pageNumber="249">Bolivia</collectingCountry>
. According to the original description, the Chilean exemplars were collected by the German-Chilean paleontologist and zoologist Rudolph Amandus Philippi (1808–1904). Philippi left his native 
<collectingCountry id="749C079FC502BD43FC23F8BB5561F884" box="[929,1033,1815,1841]" name="Germany" pageId="18" pageNumber="249">Germany</collectingCountry>
as a young man and moved to 
<taxonomicName id="CB8B3C8CC502BD43FAEBF8BB51BAF8E0" authorityName="Urban" authorityYear="1989" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Santiago" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="259" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Santiago</taxonomicName>
, 
<collectingCountry id="749C079FC502BD43FF5CF8975073F8E0" box="[222,283,1851,1877]" name="Chile" pageId="18" pageNumber="249">Chile</collectingCountry>
in 1851. There, he became professor of botany and zoology and the director of the Museo de Historia Natural (
<bibRefCitation id="681A3AFEC502BD43FF7BF8F350EEF8CC" author="Cortes, R." box="[249,390,1887,1913]" pageId="18" pageNumber="249" refId="ref21223" refString="Cortes, R. (1973) La ensenanza de la Entomologia en las universidades chilenas. 1 ª Reunion Nacional de Profesores de Fitopatologia, Entomologia y terapeutica Vegetal de las Universidades Chilenas, Chillan, 57 pp." type="book" year="1973">Cortés 1973</bibRefCitation>
). One of the 
<typeStatus id="D330F9ADC502BD43FD91F8F3531DF8CC" box="[531,629,1887,1913]" pageId="18" pageNumber="249">syntypes</typeStatus>
was found in 
<collectionCode id="6A9ADFCAC502BD43FC93F8F35226F8CC" box="[785,846,1887,1913]" country="Germany" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/8syf-d21i" name="Museum für Naturkunde Berlin (Zoological Collections)" pageId="18" pageNumber="249" type="Museum">ZMB</collectionCode>
and it was studied by 
<bibRefCitation id="681A3AFEC502BD43FBC1F8F35580F8CC" author="Zanella, F. C. V." box="[1091,1256,1887,1913]" pageId="18" pageNumber="249" pagination="435 - 488" refId="ref24081" refString="Zanella, F. C. V. (2002) Sistematica, filogenia e distribuicao geografica das especies sul-americanas de Centris (Paracentris) Cameron, 1903 e de Centris (Penthemisia) Moure, 1950, incluindo uma analise filogenetica do grupo Centris, sensu Ayala, 1998 (Hymenoptera: Apoidea: Centridini). Revista Brasileira de Entomologia, 46 (4), 435 - 488. https: // doi. org / 10.1590 / s 0085 - 56262002000400001" type="journal article" year="2002">Zanella (2002)</bibRefCitation>
who designated it as the 
<typeStatus id="D330F9ADC502BD43FF7AF82F500AF828" box="[248,354,1923,1949]" pageId="18" pageNumber="249">lectotype</typeStatus>
. The specimen has the following data label: 1598 [handwritten]\ 
<taxonomicName id="CB8B3C8CC502BD43FBC1F82F5581F828" authority="Vivallo, 2020" authorityName="Vivallo" authorityYear="2020" box="[1091,1257,1923,1949]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Centris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="249" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="smithii" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis id="3EFF9B1DC502BD43FBC1F82F5581F828" box="[1091,1257,1923,1949]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="249">Centris smithii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="25CC2666C502BD43FB70F82F5446F828" box="[1266,1326,1923,1949]" pageId="18" pageNumber="249" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
<specimenCount id="1A8D8C86C502BD43FAB4F82F5423F828" box="[1334,1355,1923,1949]" pageId="18" pageNumber="249" type="male">♂</specimenCount>
[hand-written] det. Friese 1898 [printed]\ [red label] Type [printed]\ Zool. Mus. Berlin [printed with blue ink]\ [pink label] 
<typeStatus id="D330F9ADC502BD43FF15F867505FF850" box="[151,311,1995,2021]" pageId="18" pageNumber="249">LECTOTYPE</typeStatus>
<taxonomicName id="CB8B3C8CC502BD43FEBCF8675383F850" authority=", Friese F. Zanella, 1998" authorityName=", Friese F. Zanella" authorityYear="1998" box="[318,747,1995,2021]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Centris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="249" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="smithi">
<emphasis id="3EFF9B1DC502BD43FEBCF86750B3F850" box="[318,475,1995,2021]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="249">Centris smithi</emphasis>
, Friese F. Zanella, 1998
</taxonomicName>
(
<collectionCode id="6A9ADFCAC502BD43FD78F8675254F850" box="[762,828,1995,2021]" country="Germany" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/8syf-d21i" name="Museum für Naturkunde Berlin (Zoological Collections)" pageId="18" pageNumber="249" type="Museum">ZMB</collectionCode>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="0C34470FC503BD42FF45FF3B559BFEA8" blockId="19.[151,1437,150,321]" pageId="19" pageNumber="250">
<emphasis id="3EFF9B1DC503BD42FF45FF3B5002FF05" bold="true" box="[199,362,150,177]" pageId="19" pageNumber="250">Type locality:</emphasis>
<materialsCitation id="BCE34D52C503BD42FEF3FF3B5587FEA8" ID-GBIF-Occurrence="3014903364" country="Chile" location="Chile" pageId="19" pageNumber="250" specimenCount="2" typeStatus="lectotype">
<bibRefCitation id="681A3AFEC503BD42FEF3FF3B5370FF04" author="Zanella, F. C. V." box="[369,536,151,177]" pageId="19" pageNumber="250" pagination="435 - 488" refId="ref24081" refString="Zanella, F. C. V. (2002) Sistematica, filogenia e distribuicao geografica das especies sul-americanas de Centris (Paracentris) Cameron, 1903 e de Centris (Penthemisia) Moure, 1950, incluindo uma analise filogenetica do grupo Centris, sensu Ayala, 1998 (Hymenoptera: Apoidea: Centridini). Revista Brasileira de Entomologia, 46 (4), 435 - 488. https: // doi. org / 10.1590 / s 0085 - 56262002000400001" type="journal article" year="2002">Zanella (2002)</bibRefCitation>
mentioned the type locality as “ 
<collectingCountry id="749C079FC503BD42FC01FF3B52AEFF04" box="[899,966,151,177]" name="Chile" pageId="19" pageNumber="250">Chile</collectingCountry>
”, but it cannot be inferred from the labels of the 
<typeStatus id="D330F9ADC503BD42FF60FF175024FF60" box="[226,332,187,213]" pageId="19" pageNumber="250">lectotype</typeStatus>
. He interpreted that the specimen was collected in that country assuming that the exemplar from 
<collectingCountry id="749C079FC503BD42FF15FF735181FF4C" box="[151,233,223,249]" name="Bolivia" pageId="19" pageNumber="250">Bolivia</collectingCountry>
belongs to a different species because 
<taxonomicName id="CB8B3C8CC503BD42FD1CFF735248FF4C" authorityName="Moure" authorityYear="1950" baseAuthorityName="Spinola" baseAuthorityYear="1851" box="[670,800,223,249]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Centris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="250" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="chilensis">
<emphasis id="3EFF9B1DC503BD42FD1CFF7353D9FF4C" box="[670,689,223,249]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="250">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="3EFF9B1DC503BD42FD3CFF735248FF4C" box="[702,800,223,249]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="250">chilensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is supposedly restricted to 
<collectingCountry id="749C079FC503BD42FBD0FF7355FAFF4C" box="[1106,1170,223,249]" name="Chile" pageId="19" pageNumber="250">Chile</collectingCountry>
. Unfortunately, the current condition and depository of the 
<typeStatus id="D330F9ADC503BD42FDADFEAF53AEFEA8" box="[559,710,259,285]" pageId="19" pageNumber="250">paralectotype</typeStatus>
from 
<collectingCountry id="749C079FC503BD42FC88FEAF5237FEA8" box="[778,863,259,285]" name="Bolivia" pageId="19" pageNumber="250">Bolivia</collectingCountry>
, as well as the others, are unknown
</materialsCitation>
.
</paragraph>
